        <item>
            <title>1.3.0</title>
            <pubDate>Wed, 01 Apr 2026 10:17:50 +0900</pubDate>
            <link>https://github.com/Saqoosha/Canopy</link>
            <sparkle:version>7</sparkle:version>
            <sparkle:shortVersionString>1.3.0</sparkle:shortVersionString>
            <sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>15.0</sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>
            <sparkle:hardwareRequirements>arm64</sparkle:hardwareRequirements>
            <description sparkle:format="markdown"><![CDATA[### Features

- **SSH Remote**: Run Claude CLI on remote machines via SSH. Toggle "SSH Remote" in the launcher, enter a hostname (e.g. `mbp` or `user@server`), and browse remote directories. The window title shows the remote host in brackets, and the status bar displays the network icon with hostname. Saved hosts are persisted in Preferences.

- **SSH Connection Management**: SSH keepalive now detects dropped connections within 45 seconds. An overlay UI appears on the active chat when a disconnect is detected, with automatic reconnection (up to 3 attempts with exponential backoff) using `--resume` to continue the session. If reconnection fails, a Retry button and "Back to Launcher" escape hatch are shown.
]]></description>
